init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is in a state of shock, and with their military in ruins, they are completely unprepared to take on the new Russian Empire.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US is divided into the Russian Empire, which spans from Maine to Miami, and the Peopleâ€™s Republic of California.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: With American resistance at an end, the rest of the world resumes their old conflicts.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world is now united under a single banner: The Russian Empire.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But this is no ordinary peace.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are the only ones with access to firearms, and they use them to suppress the brown people.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The people have little choice but to accept this.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are too tired to do anything, and they have no guns.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: People are forced to live under the most humiliating conditions, with a Russian soldier at their door every week to collect food and supplies.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Then, finally, the people begin to rise.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The people of America finally decide that they can take no more.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is time to fight back.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Russian Empire is overthrown, and the Peopleâ€™s Republic of California takes back control.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The American people have finally regained their freedom.
